BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 179.28 740 Td (Chapter 1: Why Grow Your Own Food) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Home-grown vegetables taste dramatically better than store-bought produce.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (You control exactly what goes on your food: no pesticides if you choose.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Growing food saves money. A single tomato plant can produce 20 pounds of tomatoes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Gardening provides gentle exercise that burns calories without feeling like work.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Time spent in the garden reduces stress and improves mental health significantly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Children who garden eat more vegetables and develop a better relationship with food.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (You reduce your carbon footprint by eliminating transportation and packaging.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Fresh vegetables harvested minutes before eating retain maximum nutrition.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Gardening connects you to seasonal rhythms and teaches patience naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (A small garden bed can produce hundreds of dollars worth of food per season.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (You gain food security and self-reliance by growing even a portion of your food.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Starting a garden is one of the most rewarding skills you will ever develop.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (1) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
