BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 163.92000000000002 740 Td (Chapter 2: Planning Your Garden Space) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Most vegetables need at least six to eight hours of direct sunlight daily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Observe your yard throughout the day to identify the sunniest spots.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Start small: a 4 by 4 foot raised bed is perfect for a first garden.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Raised beds offer better drainage, fewer weeds, and easier access.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (You can also garden in containers on a patio, balcony, or driveway.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Place your garden near a water source to make watering convenient.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Avoid areas under large trees where roots compete for water and nutrients.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (South-facing locations receive the most sunlight in the northern hemisphere.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Level ground prevents water from running off before soaking in.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Consider proximity to your kitchen since you will harvest daily when producing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Sketch a simple map of your space noting sun exposure and dimensions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Good planning before planting prevents problems and wasted effort later.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
