BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 133.20000000000002 740 Td (Chapter 5: Starting from Seeds vs Transplants) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Seeds are cheaper and offer far more variety than nursery transplants.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Transplants give you a head start and are easier for absolute beginners.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Some crops must be direct-seeded: carrots, beans, peas, and radishes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Some crops benefit from indoor starting: tomatoes, peppers, and eggplant.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Start seeds indoors six to eight weeks before your transplant date outside.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Seeds need warmth, moisture, and light to germinate successfully.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Use seed starting mix, not garden soil, for indoor seed starting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Place seed trays near a sunny south-facing window or under grow lights.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Keep soil consistently moist but not waterlogged during germination.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Harden off indoor seedlings by gradually exposing them to outdoor conditions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Move transplants outside for one hour the first day, increasing daily for a week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Direct-seeded crops are simpler: just plant the seed in the ground and water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (5) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
