BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 198.48000000000002 740 Td (Chapter 7: Watering Properly) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Most vegetables need one to two inches of water per week from rain or irrigation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Water deeply and less frequently rather than shallow daily sprinklings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Deep watering encourages roots to grow down where moisture is more consistent.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Water in the morning so leaves dry during the day, preventing disease.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Avoid wetting foliage. Water at the base of plants whenever possible.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Drip irrigation or soaker hoses deliver water directly to roots efficiently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Mulch around plants with straw or wood chips to retain soil moisture.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Stick your finger two inches into soil. If dry at that depth, water immediately.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Container gardens need more frequent watering, often daily in hot weather.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Wilting in afternoon heat is normal but wilting in morning means water is needed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Overwatering causes root rot which kills plants faster than underwatering.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Consistent watering prevents problems like blossom end rot on tomatoes and peppers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
