BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 183.12 740 Td (Chapter 8: Fertilizing Naturally) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Plants need three main nutrients: nitrogen, phosphorus, and potassium \(N-P-K\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Nitrogen promotes leaf growth and green color for leafy vegetables.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Phosphorus supports root development and fruit production.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Potassium strengthens overall plant health and disease resistance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Compost provides a balanced, slow-release supply of all essential nutrients.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Add compost as a side dressing around plants every four to six weeks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Fish emulsion is an excellent liquid organic fertilizer for quick feeding.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Worm castings are gentle and can be applied without risk of burning plants.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Bone meal adds phosphorus for strong roots and better fruit set.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Blood meal adds nitrogen for leafy greens that need extra green growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Avoid over-fertilizing which can burn plants and create excess leaf growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Feed the soil with organic matter and the soil will feed your plants naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
