BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 148.56 740 Td (Chapter 9: Dealing with Pests Organically) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Prevention is the best pest management: healthy plants resist pests naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Inspect plants regularly so you catch pest problems before they become severe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Handpick large pests like caterpillars, slugs, and beetles into soapy water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (A strong spray of water from the hose knocks off aphids and spider mites.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Neem oil spray works against a wide range of soft-bodied insect pests.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Diatomaceous earth sprinkled around plants deters slugs and crawling insects.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Row covers physically block flying pests from reaching your plants.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Companion planting with marigolds, basil, and herbs repels many common pests.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Attract beneficial insects like ladybugs and lacewings that eat pest insects.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Plant flowers near your garden to support beneficial predator populations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Rotating crops yearly prevents pest populations from building up in soil.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Accept minor pest damage. A few holes in leaves do not ruin the harvest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (9) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
