BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 167.76 740 Td (Chapter 10: Companion Planting Guide) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Companion planting pairs crops that benefit each other when grown nearby.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Tomatoes grow well with basil which may improve flavor and repel pests.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Carrots and onions planted together confuse each other's pest flies.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Corn, beans, and squash \(the three sisters\) support each other symbiotically.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Beans fix nitrogen that corn and squash use. Corn supports bean vines.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Squash leaves shade the ground reducing weeds for all three crops.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Marigolds planted throughout the garden repel nematodes and many insects.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Avoid planting tomatoes near brassicas \(broccoli, cabbage\) as they inhibit growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Keep fennel away from most vegetables as it suppresses their growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Lettuce grows well in the shade of taller plants like tomatoes in summer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Radishes planted with slower crops like carrots mark rows and break up soil.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Experiment with companion planting and note what works in your specific garden.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (10) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
