BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 186.96 740 Td (Chapter 11: Container Gardening) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Containers let you garden anywhere: patios, balconies, driveways, and porches.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Almost any vegetable can grow in a container if the pot is large enough.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Use pots at least 12 inches deep and wide for most vegetables.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Tomatoes, peppers, and eggplant need five-gallon containers minimum.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Herbs, lettuce, and radishes grow happily in smaller containers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Ensure every container has drainage holes to prevent waterlogged roots.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Use potting mix, not garden soil, which is too heavy and drains poorly in pots.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Containers dry out faster than ground beds so check water needs daily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Self-watering containers reduce watering frequency with built-in reservoirs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Feed container plants every two weeks since watering flushes nutrients out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Group containers together for an attractive display and easier watering.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Container gardening is perfect for renters who cannot dig in-ground beds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
