BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 190.8 740 Td (Chapter 12: Vertical Gardening) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Vertical gardening grows plants upward on supports to save ground space.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Cucumbers, peas, beans, and small melons all climb trellises naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (A simple trellis can be made from wood stakes and twine for under ten dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Cattle panels bent into arches create beautiful and productive tunnel trellises.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Vertical growing improves air circulation which reduces fungal disease.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Plants grown vertically receive more even sunlight on all their leaves.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Harvesting is easier when fruits hang at eye level instead of ground level.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Tomato cages support indeterminate tomatoes that grow six feet or taller.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (String trellising uses overhead strings that vines climb up naturally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Stacking raised beds or using wall planters maximizes tiny spaces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Even a blank fence or wall can support climbing vegetables with hooks and wire.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Vertical gardens can triple your harvest in the same footprint of ground space.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (12) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
