q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Most vegetables last longest stored in the refrigerator crisper drawer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Tomatoes should never be refrigerated as cold destroys their flavor and texture.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Root vegetables like carrots and beets store for months in a cool dark place.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Freezing preserves vegetables for six to twelve months with minimal effort.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Blanch vegetables briefly in boiling water before freezing to preserve color.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Canning allows you to store tomato sauce, pickles, and salsa for over a year.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Dehydrating herbs and vegetables concentrates flavor and requires no refrigeration.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Garlic and onions cure in a warm dry place for two weeks then store for months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Winter squash cures similarly and stores three to six months at room temperature.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Pickling cucumbers, peppers, and green beans preserves them deliciously.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Share excess harvest with neighbors, food banks, or community refrigerators.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Proper storage ensures you enjoy your garden harvest long after the season ends.) Tj ET
