BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Late winter: order seeds, plan your garden layout, start tomatoes indoors.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Early spring: start peppers indoors, prepare beds, plant peas and greens outside.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Mid spring: transplant cold-hardy crops, direct-sow beets, carrots, and radishes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Late spring: after last frost, transplant tomatoes, peppers, and plant beans.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Early summer: plant squash, cucumbers, and succession-sow lettuce for continuous harvest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Midsummer: harvest heavily, water consistently, plant fall crops like kale and broccoli.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Late summer: start fall lettuce, plant garlic cloves for next year's harvest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Early fall: harvest remaining warm-season crops before first frost arrives.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Mid fall: plant garlic, add compost to empty beds, plant cover crops.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Late fall: mulch beds heavily, clean and store tools, reflect on the season.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Winter: plan next year's garden, order seeds early, repair raised beds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Each season offers gardening tasks that prepare you for the next productive cycle.) Tj ET
